description.narrative:
Build a scalable and replicable model to provide small holder farmers in Indonesia with access to the digital economy, in order to improve farmer productivity and increase incomes.

1. Build on Bank Andara’s “Andara Link” digital payment platform to enable effective payments for agricultural value chain transactions through local MFIs and agribusinesses close to farmers;
2. Link core agricultural buyers, processors and input supplier payments to Andara Link to serve millions of rural clients;
3. Actively engage farmer cooperatives and agribusinesses across Java, to build sound implementation practices around digital agricultural value chain payments; 
4. Measure impact of payments on farmer productivity and profits, and build case studies around models to connect members of the rural economy to commercial payment platforms.
